   {
      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "From my understanding \"-discover\" is a boolean argument. In this case the proposed change would not make sense.\n=&lt;n&gt; is meant to be for parameters that take a numeric value.\n\nThough I agree that -discover=0 to disable a boolean option is a little bit confusing. So maybe we should avoid boolean options with default=1 in general, and always provide the opposite: \"-nodiscover\" in this case. We already have implemented InterpretNegativeSetting in util.cpp to actually support \"-nodiscover\". So I suggest considering this as a general issue with boolean arguments defaulting to 1 and rework them in general in a separate pull request.\n",
      "created_at" : "2014-03-04T13:08:33Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/3793#issuecomment-36621868",
