      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Funny that you think discovery is \"very special cases\" when it's likely the majority of hosts. Discovery doesn't just cover the external IP service, it also covers UPNP discovery (which also covers the firewall cases).  There are incomplete patches floating around which eliminate the service usage and instead use other Bitcoin nodes to accomplish discovery.\n\nI have no opinion on the parameter description nitpicking. I'm just commenting to clear up confusion about what the behavior is used for...\n",
